Title: I will color correct, colour grade, and enhance the visual look for your video
Description:
Before ordering send me a link where I can see your project and I will come back to you so we can discuss steps necessary to take and work out the pricing.

**COLOR CORRECTION**is the process where every clip is manually tweaked to get proper exposure and balance of light. Each clip is adjusted to match color temperature to a predefined choice for each scene.

**COLOR GRADING**¬†is the creative process where decisions are made to further enhance or establish a new visual tone to the project through software including introducing new color themes, re-lighting within a frame, films stock emulations, color gradients and a lot of other choices.

**BRIEFING,**¬†send me a short description of your creative idea.¬†Screenshots from videos or photographs which could work as good references include any other information which would help us communicate and build the look for your film.

This¬†article might be a good read before the first colour grading session:¬†¬†http://filmmakermagazine.com/87033-how-to-survive-first-color-grade/#.WeCw9BNSxmM

Hi! I am a **colorist** expert and **filmmaker**, specializing in color correction and grading services for **short films and feature film**. *Contact me before placing an order.*

Color grading sets the **tone and mood** of a film. For example, warm colors can evoke feelings of comfort and nostalgia, while cooler tones can create a sense of unease or sadness.

**Colors influence viewers' emotions** and **enhance storytelling** by aligning the visual tone with the narrative.

Proper color grading can turn ordinary footage into something **visually stunning**. It enhances the overall aesthetic quality, making the film more appealing to the audience.

*As a filmmaker*, I know that visually stunning footage that truly captures the essence and vision is essential.
